6) hopefully we can look back at this prediction a year from now and lol at it.

5) if more trusted global payment networks begins to achieve widespread adoption it will cause major anxiety for the US and threaten the dollars status as the reserve currency of the world. This situation could unfold rather quickly (approx 3 years) if Russia does invade Ukraine

4) maybe this will spur crypto adoption and utilization on a national level. This could happen long term. Short term I think the global payment network will start to fragment and there will be more than 5 or more trusted options to transfer money outside of the SWIFT network.

3) I think that a majority of the world will look negatively on the US excluding Russia from the SWIFT payment network. Nations and foreign banks will start to seriously consider using alternative methods for transferring money around the globe.

2) I don‚Äôt think that the US will ‚Äúban‚Äù crypto or fiat on ramps. I do think the US will try to ‚Äúban‚Äù Centralized Exchanges from allowing users to transfer their assets ‚Äúon chain‚Äù.  I think this could happen regardless of the Russia situation. Now back to geopolitics‚Ä¶

1) Prediction time: if Russia does invade Ukraine and the U.S. unilaterally decides to exclude Russia from the SWIFT payment network it will be the catalyst for heavy handed crypto regulation coming out of Washington in the name of ‚Äúnational security‚Äù.
